File: Pitso Mosimane, coach of Mamelodi Sundowns. JOHANNESBURG - Pitso Mosimane has been announced as the head coach of Egytian giants, Al Ahly. The announcement was made on Al Ahly's Twitter account on Thursday. READ: Mosimane reportedly leaves Sundowns Mosimane announced his departure from Mamelodi Sundowns on Wednesday after almost eight years at the club. 'Jingles' led Sundowns to a domestic treble last season winning the Absa Premiership, Telkom Knockout and Nedbank Cup, all in a single campaign. He ends his almost eight-year tenure at the Brazilians having led the club to continental success, winning the CAF Champions League in 2016.